// agent/models.json — pi custom model registry
//
// Pi's built-in `github-copilot` provider catalog is hardcoded per pi release
// (docs/providers.md: "For each provider, pi knows all available models. The
// list is updated with every pi release."). This file lets us add Copilot
// models ahead of the next pi release using pi's documented merge-by-id
// semantics:
//
//   - Built-in models are kept.
//   - Custom models are upserted by `id` within the provider.
//   - If a custom model `id` matches a built-in model `id`, the custom model
//     replaces that built-in model.
//   - If a custom model `id` is new, it is added alongside built-in models.
//
// Prerequisite for any new Copilot model: it must be enabled in the VS Code
// Copilot Chat model picker (Settings → Models → Manage). The Copilot proxy
// will not serve a model your account has not enabled there, regardless of
// what this file says.
//
// Upstream tier gates: Copilot subscription tier (free / pro / pro+ /
// business / enterprise / max) gates which models the proxy will serve. A
// model excluded from your tier (e.g. MAI-Code-1-Flash on enterprise as of
// 2026-06-07) cannot be unlocked locally; no models.json entry will help.
//
// To add a model, uncomment the github-copilot block below and append an
// entry with at minimum `id` and `name`. The full schema is in the installed
// pi package: <pi_install>/docs/models.md ("Model Configuration" table).
// Pi requires any provider object to specify at least one of `baseUrl`,
// `headers`, `compat`, `modelOverrides`, or a non-empty `models` array — an
// empty stub block is rejected at load time, so we leave the block out
// entirely until a model is actually being added.
//
// Verify after editing: `pi --list-models <pattern>` should resolve the new
// id. JSONC comments and trailing commas are supported.
//
// Example (do not enable until the model is exposed by Copilot to your tier
// AND enabled in your VS Code Copilot Chat picker):
//
//   "providers": {
//     "github-copilot": {
//       "models": [
//         {
//           "id": "mai-code-1-flash",
//           "name": "MAI Code 1 Flash",
//           "reasoning": false,
//           "input": ["text"],
//           "contextWindow": 200000,
//           "maxTokens": 16384
//         }
//       ]
//     }
//   }
//
// See: ADR-0026 (forward-fix pattern).
{
  "providers": {}
}
